title: How has the number of ambulance staff changed over time?
analysis_commentary:
The number of ambulance staff in England has been above 17,000 since October 2009 and numbers remained relatively steady until September 2015. Since then there has been a noticeable rise in the number of ambulance staff to 19,720 as of January 2017.

Updated April 2017.
